Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.67,0:00:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's okay"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.63,0:00:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.94,0:00:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean that I want you to stop \N the investigation I requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.85,0:00:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.60,0:00:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the investigation into Karl Neumann is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.56,0:00:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.35,0:00:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, just hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.13,0:00:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't learned everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.90,0:00:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is still the possibility that Edmund \N Fahren, who claimed to be your son...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...didn't actually commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still haven't found the person \N who was controlling Fahren!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.54,0:00:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything has been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.63,0:00:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tea is ready, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.63,0:00:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.56,0:01:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.39,0:01:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.10,0:01:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Send me the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.36,0:01:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather is nice today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.61,0:01:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.15,0:01:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.28,0:01:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Johan is here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.37,0:01:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ice cold, solitary man who didn't believe in anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...turned into a  good natured \N old man after finding his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.71,0:01:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.71,0:01:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he was once called the Vampire of Bayern...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.59,0:01:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I see.  So Johan is here, too?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.67,0:03:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.10,0:03:27.77,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,67)\pos(351,330)}Just One Case
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.52,0:03:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're running around trying to find a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that my client's ex-husband kidnapped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like parental custody of dogs can also be a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.81,0:03:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, I'm going to have some wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.19,0:03:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water is enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.19,0:03:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you are taking a small \N break from your line of work...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.15,0:03:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it doesn't appear that you are \N letting alcohol concern you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:03:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm perfectly okay on that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.95,0:04:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that point?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.58,0:04:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something else on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.79,0:04:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now that I have some spare \N time, I'm doing some silly things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.46,0:04:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.46,0:04:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking through my case scrapbooks \N that I made when I was still a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.51,0:04:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones that were unsolved...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.64,0:04:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.43,0:04:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how do you feel when you look through them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.64,0:04:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm mortified!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.94,0:04:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the thought of killers living casually out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.44,0:04:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel really helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.03,0:04:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At my lack of ability, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.41,0:04:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did have the ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.41,0:04:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Richard...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.70,0:04:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you were trying too hard, you \N identified with the cases far too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.68,0:04:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your irritation at your inability to read \N the killers' minds became frustration...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I turned to alcohol..
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, food time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.64,0:05:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I don't think it was a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.14,0:05:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking through your old case scrapbooks...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It just irritates me even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to tell me what you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.28,0:05:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...now that you're looking through \N them with your new point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.53,0:05:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got drunk and shot that youth, who was a serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are now prepared to face that truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still running away...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...from remembering what was going through \N your mind when you pulled that trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.68,0:05:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can still see him, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.68,0:05:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kid's ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.89,0:05:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.98,0:05:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When everything becomes clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...when everything is revealed by daylight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.27,0:05:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that ghost will disappear as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.94,0:06:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring everything into the daylight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of Holmer the Accountant."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim, Joachim Holmer, had a solid career...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and wasn't the type to be the target of anyone's hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he was stabbed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.43,0:06:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of robbery...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.08,0:06:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the Voice of God."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victims were a former house maid and a driver...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.98,0:07:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In both cases, there was a message that read "I \N heard the voice of God" written on the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the President \N of the Dolnach Company."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Rudy Gauck, a prominent, wealthy man in Bayern...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was found dead in the Hartholz forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.28,0:07:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the Spillers."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.90,0:07:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The drowned bodies of a middle aged couple \N  were found upstream in the Isar River...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Currently under investigation in connection with the \N ongoing serial murders of middled aged couples...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.87,0:07:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main suspect, the Japanese doctor, is still on the run...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.63,0:07:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.30,0:07:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more unsolved cases I had, the more I drank...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.56,0:07:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like the doctor said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.23,0:07:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what it's like to think without \N being under the influence...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.36,0:08:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on a second...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.42,0:08:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think carefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think carefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What passed through your mind then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.61,0:08:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's the thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking of something, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw the boy's ghost and you forgot \N what you were thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.37,0:08:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need to rush things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.08,0:09:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, the thought will come back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was I thinking about...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.89,0:09:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An important key to solving one of the unsolved cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just my imagination...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.45,0:09:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.50,0:09:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's following me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.51,0:09:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exactly like that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.88,0:09:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.09,0:09:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I was running down an alley like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...chasing after him, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to come here so late, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you've decided to tell me everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, I saw it inside that kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.67,0:10:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I realized it does exist in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pure evil...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.78,0:10:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.53,0:10:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.31,0:10:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...shot and killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good, I'm glad you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really gotten back on your feet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there is still more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That thing I thought of the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.45,0:10:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The many unsolved cases I left behind, they're actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.83,0:10:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just one case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.13,0:11:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Dr. Gillen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.67,0:11:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The literary work you sent me the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.90,0:11:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A Transcendental Criminal Psychological Outline."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.93,0:11:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I read it with great interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one of my students from my days \N of teaching at Düsseldorf University...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.62,0:11:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is writing works like this fills me with great joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Dr. Gillen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.19,0:11:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You once told me of your interview with \N the serial murderer, Peter Jurgens...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.68,0:11:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, Jurgens said to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that he committed a murder because \N a certain "friend" ordered him to, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.73,0:11:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because I can't recall the details, would \N you mind telling me the story again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.59,0:11:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of Jurgens' "friend," that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.31,0:12:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were an excellent student when \N you were in college, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.98,0:12:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there was also another outstanding student who seemed \N to be competing with you for the top seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.74,0:12:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He now walks the path of a neurosurgeon, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.74,0:12:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he's a material witness in the case of the serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to tell me anything you can about \N him, no matter how little it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person was he..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.59,0:12:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and where he is now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.71,0:12:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man named Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.05,0:12:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're that detective from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm just a poor private investigator now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.39,0:12:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a painful story, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.94,0:12:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...may I ask you about the "Voice of God" \N murder case your mother was involved in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.44,0:12:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.99,0:12:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been four years now, and the police aren't putting \N any effort into the investigation anymore, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.66,0:13:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that your mother used to be \N a maid for that wealthy man...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.04,0:13:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but that was twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she quit for any reason in particular?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor health, mainly...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.34,0:13:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, she only did work around the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any chance she didn't get along with Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.10,0:13:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, my mother loved to read him poems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when Mr. Schuwald could still see, \N the two used to recite to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.41,0:13:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.00,0:13:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They remind me of my mother, \N so I've kept them all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.27,0:13:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each poetry anthology on these shelves was \N given to my mother by Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe the officer in charge of the \N case of Dolnach's president's murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is a mere detective now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.73,0:14:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is something I want to ask you about, \N since you were the president's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding anyone who hated the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The president's enemies...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.15,0:14:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that we'd never stop \N counting if we started, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.22,0:14:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The list of companies President \N Gauck sent into bankruptcy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...should have already been analyzed by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.83,0:14:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is another wealthy, powerful \N person in Bayern, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.67,0:14:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was their relationship like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.88,0:14:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.47,0:14:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were rivals, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lifelong, might I add.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.60,0:14:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.60,0:14:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald has declared bankruptcy twice in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.19,0:14:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His second bankruptcy was the result of a fierce \N competition between him and President Gauck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.36,0:15:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Mr. Schuwald \N was crushed by the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, there were times when \N the president was beaten by Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.16,0:15:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two hated each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.29,0:15:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.93,0:15:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be bad if they saw other other at a party!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.71,0:15:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two liked to express their feelings verbally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.13,0:15:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, those two cold hearted people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.76,0:15:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two were the only ones who could \N match each other in an argument...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.53,0:15:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than just rivals...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.10,0:15:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they were actually friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.84,0:15:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.80,0:16:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hans?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.30,0:16:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew him very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.51,0:16:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was one of the two victims involved \N in the "Voice of God" murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.56,0:16:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a good person.  I felt sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was that good of a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.75,0:16:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he used to treat me to drinks quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.74,0:16:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to be Mr. Schuwald's driver, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.66,0:16:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was thirty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.25,0:16:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why he was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.71,0:16:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Schuwald went bankrupt at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.13,0:16:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.67,0:16:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't cause any trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.72,0:16:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I'm going to say this in honor of Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.47,0:16:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't matter if the person was an ass with \N a boatload of money, or poor like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the type of person who \N could get along with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to tell us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.19,0:17:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that he was the one who taught \N that rich guy how to bird watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.57,0:17:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bird watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.45,0:17:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.12,0:17:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hans said that when he brought him to the forest, he \N was as happy as a child, and didn't act like a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's been two years since the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.79,0:17:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I still remember what happened to my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was a very serious person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't do anything that people would hate him for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet... the way he was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.01,0:17:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my sympathies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.31,0:17:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but I think your husband was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was young, he grew up in an orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.44,0:17:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and went from foster home to foster home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.98,0:17:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After a lot of hard work, he became an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband received a request to become \N Schuwald's financial adviser, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.12,0:17:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, several times...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he turned them all down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:17:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that he was too busy with his current job, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he said that his philosophy on money was different from Schuwald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.21,0:18:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was very fastidious with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.40,0:18:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.01,0:18:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you catch the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.01,0:18:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.47,0:18:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll be caught!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.23,0:18:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.02,0:18:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you happen to know how your husband \N became acquainted with Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.17,0:18:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he said they met in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.32,0:18:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the forest...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was when Mr. Schuwald could still see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They met in the forest by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.12,0:18:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was he there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.54,0:18:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went to bird watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.54,0:18:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, they went together several more times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.97,0:18:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bird watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.31,0:18:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy like a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.89,0:19:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Recite to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.90,0:19:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.08,0:19:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, I'm fine.  Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.79,0:19:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a horrible driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.96,0:19:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looked like he was actually aiming for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.51,0:19:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it all figured out, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.07,0:19:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like I told you the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.14,0:19:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the cases I was in charge of when I was still an officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.06,0:19:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were related in some way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.36,0:19:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the Voice of God."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.69,0:19:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the President \N of the Dolnach Company."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.49,0:19:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of an Accountant."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.86,0:19:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At a glance, these cases don't seem to be related.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.12,0:20:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victims were murdered in different ways, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.66,0:20:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the victims were unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.08,0:20:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, because there were no fiscal connections...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.38,0:20:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the truth was never recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.96,0:20:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all connected at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.05,0:20:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victims' deaths in every case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.01,0:20:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were all done to isolate Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is another strange common point...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.77,0:20:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the murder case of Dolnach Company president...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.11,0:20:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...right before the crime took place...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...President Gauck left, saying that he \N had an important business meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of the person he was going to meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.78,0:20:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the name of God that was written \N on the wall by the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.99,0:20:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the "Voice of God" murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And amongst the cases I was in charge of...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.12,0:20:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the only case that seemed to be unrelated...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.83,0:20:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murder Case of the Middle Aged Couple."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.59,0:20:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of the killer the Japanese doctor \N spoke of during his questioning...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are all the same name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:20:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.02,0:21:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A criminal psychological scholar who \N used to be a student of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is studying a killer who said he committed his \N crime because of an order from a "friend"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.86,0:21:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me everything in a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of that "friend" was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.88,0:21:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a common name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The connection in every case may be mere speculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.00,0:21:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if you really are correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.79,0:21:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He planned each murder in the past \N four years and committed each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.84,0:21:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person calling himself "Johan" \N has completely isolated Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.03,0:21:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And luckily for him, the prostitute named Margo \N Langer who gave birth to Schuwald's son is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.77,0:21:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Fahren student who claimed to be Schuwald's son...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.77,0:21:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just happened to commit suicide right \N before the appearance of his real son.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.21,0:21:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he really does exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.20,0:22:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...where is this Johan right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.16,0:22:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Johan is here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.05,0:22:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.84,0:22:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice weather today, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.01,0:22:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right next to Schuwald!
